### Description

We are copy a text to clipboard using the Clipboard.SetDataObject method. Then when we retrieve the data from the clipboard using the Clipboard.GetDataObject method, the data not valid exception is thrown in the .NET9 preview 6 version.

```
 //Clear the existing data in the clipboard
 Clipboard.Clear();
IDataObject dataObject = new DataObject();
 dataObject.SetData("TextInfo", "I have copied this");
 //Set the data in the clipboard
 Clipboard.SetDataObject(dataObject, true);

 //Retrieve the data from the clipboard
 IDataObject retrievedDataObject =Clipboard.GetDataObject();
 if (retrievedDataObject != null && retrievedDataObject.GetDataPresent("TextInfo"))
 {

    // Exception is thrown here.
     string clipboardData = (string)retrievedDataObject.GetData("TextInfo");
 }
```


### Reproduction Steps

Use the above provided code snippet in the description to reproduce the issue.

### Expected behavior

The data should be retrieved properly

